## ‚ú® Features

- üé® **Rich Logging:** Beautiful, structured logging with loguru integration, multiple output formats (rich console, JSONL, file), and customizable profiles for different environments;
- ‚è±Ô∏è **Precise Timing:** Easy-to-use timing decorators and context managers with detailed statistics (mean, median, stdev) and automatic logging integration;
- üì¶ **Multi-Format Serialization:** Unified interface for JSON, TOML, and YAML serialization with Pydantic model support and customizable encoding/decoding hooks;
- üë• **Human-Readable Formats:** Intelligent conversion of numbers, durations, and throughput into human-readable strings with appropriate units and precision;
- üîÑ **Progress Tracking:** Integrated progress bars with rich visualization, timing integration, and parallel processing support through joblib;
- ‚öôÔ∏è **Smart Configuration:** Environment-aware configuration system using Pydantic with automatic environment variable parsing and type-safe settings.

## üì¶ Installation

To install `liblaf-grapes`, run the following command:

```bash
uv add liblaf-grapes
```

## ‚å®Ô∏è Local Development

You can use Github Codespaces for online development:

[![](https://github.com/codespaces/badge.svg)](https://codespaces.new/liblaf/grapes)

Or clone it for local development:

```bash
gh repo clone liblaf/grapes
cd grapes
mise run install
```

